---
syntax: bash
tags: [ grep,ripgrep,rg,search ]
---
explanation: rga is a line-oriented search tool that allows you to look for a regex in a multitude of file types. 
             rga wraps the awesome ripgrep and enables it to search in pdf, docx, sqlite, jpg, zip, tar.*, movie subtitles (mkv, mp4), etc.

# Search pattern in PDF
rga foo /Dokument/test.pdf

# Search all file in the demo folder for hello
rga "hello" demo/

